"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433455","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-07","<p>Dedicating 20% of shop window advertising to responsible gambling messages is an industry-led initiative, introduced by the Senet Group last year.</p><p>All gambling advertising must comply with the UK Advertising Codes. These Codes include a number of requirements, such as ensuring that advertising is not aimed at children or young people and that it does not leave vulnerable people open to exploitation or harm.</p><p>More generally, the Gambling Commission’s Licence conditions and codes of practice (LCCP) require that all gambling advertising should be undertaken in a socially responsible manner.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2015-12-07T17:08:18.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433455/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433455/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433455/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-12-01","Betting Shops: Advertising","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what guidance his Department gives to betting companies on the nature of their messages about responsible gambling required in their shop window advertising.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","18387"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433456","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-07","<p>The Government, along with the Gambling Commission, is in the process of evaluating the effects of ending unsupervised stakes over £50 and we will publish the results in due course</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2015-12-07T17:10:03.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433456/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433456/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433456/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-12-01","Gaming Machines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the regulations introduced in April 2015 which ended unsupervised stakes above £50 on Fixed Odds Betting Terminals in betting shops.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","18388"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433457","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-07","<p>As at 31 October 2015 the number of Ministry of Defence civil servants in the redeployment pool was 240 (rounded to the nearest 10).</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2015-12-07T16:54:03.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433457/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433457/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433457/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-01","Ministry of Defence: Labour Mobility","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many civil servants in his Department are in the redeployment pool.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","18336"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433458","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-08","<p>The Royal Navy has attracted significant investment as a result of the Strategic Defence and Security Review, including an increase in personnel to 30,600 by 2025. This level of investment continues to ensure delivery of Continuous Carrier Capability from both Queen Elizabeth Class aircraft carriers.</p><br />","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-08T16:24:06.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433458/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433458/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433458/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-01","Aircraft Carriers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, from where the Royal Navy will attain the remaining personnel necessary to crew the two new Queen Elizabeth Class aircraft carriers; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","18258"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433459","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-04","<p>We are extremely concerned about and closely monitoring the growing threat from extremist groups in Libya, including groups affiliated with Daesh. These groups threaten Libya, her regional neighbours and UK interests in the region. We have seen barbaric and appalling acts of terror inside Libya, including the targeting of others because of their faith. Daesh continues to commit appalling atrocities, including, most recently, in Sirte.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-12-04T14:12:29.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433459/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433459/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433459/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-01","Libya: Islamic State","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what review he has conducted of the operational capacity of Islamic State in Libya; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","18324"
