"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432899","Cabinet Office","false","2015-12-02","<p>Cabinet Office will shortly issue guidance that reminds public authorities of their international obligations when letting public contracts. It will make clear that boycotts in public procurement are inappropriate and may be illegal, outside where formal legal sanctions, embargoes and restrictions have been put in place by the Government.</p><p>The Department for Communities and Local Government (DCLG) is currently working to give effect to the recent announcement on Local Government Pension Scheme funds’ investment allocations, specifically the extent to which administering authorities should have regard to non-financial factors. Guidance will be issued to local authorities in the new year.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-12-02T14:39:52.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432899/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432899/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432899/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-27","Local Government: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what plans the Government has to bring forward new regulations or guidance on divestment or boycott policies pursued by local authorities.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","18048"
