"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432913","Church Commissioners","false","2015-12-03","<p>The Diocese of Blackburn is working alongside other dioceses of the Church of England and local faith communities to coordinate their response to assist Syrian refugees. Churches in the diocese have been advised of the type of assistance that can most usefully be offered, working in conjunction with local authorities and other faith communities.</p><p /> <p>The three bishops of the Diocese of Blackburn were amongst the signatories to the letter from Church of England bishops to the Prime Minister, which welcomed the commitment of the Government to provide aid and resettlement, while calling on it to resettle substantially more than 20,000, and made clear the Church’s commitment to help in that task.</p>","Meriden","Mrs Caroline Spelman",,"2015-12-03T16:32:49.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432913/answer","Biography information for Dame Caroline Spelman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432913/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432913/answer",,,,,"9","Church Commissioners","Church Commissioners","2015-11-27","Refugees: Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the right hon. Member for Meriden, representing the Church Commissioners, what steps each Anglican church in the Diocese of Blackburn is taking to assist Syrian refugees.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","18054"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432914","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-12-02","<p>The Government has a manifesto commitment to extend the Right to Buy to housing association tenants.</p><p>The voluntary agreement we have made with the National Housing Federation will give 1.3 million housing association tenants the opportunity to buy their home with an equivalent discount to the Right to Buy, delivering the manifesto commitment.</p><p>This will include those tenants who currently have a Right to Acquire.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-12-02T15:56:23.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432914/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432914/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432914/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-11-27","Right to Acquire Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether his Department plans to make the level of discount received for tenants who exercise the Right to Acquire the same as for those who exercise the Right to Buy.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","18050"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432915","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-07","<p>As set out in the Chancellor of the Exchequer’s Autumn statement last week, there are no plans to reduce the Big Lottery Fund’s budget. The Fund will continue to receive 40% of National Lottery good cause money. Sport, Arts and Heritage will also continue to receive 20% each.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2015-12-07T15:42:55.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432915/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432915/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432915/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-11-27","Big Lottery Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment he has made of the effect of planned changes in funding for the Big Lottery Fund on local community, sport and cultural organisations.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","18037"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432916","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-03","<p>BT have confirmed that the work to provide a telephone and internet connectivity to the new build site has been completed.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-12-03T15:22:17.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432916/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432916/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432916/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-11-27","Telecommunications: Sheffield Heeley","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 15 September 2015 to Question 9695, on telecommunications: Sheffield, Heeley, whether the problem referred to has now been resolved.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","18045"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432917","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-11","<p>Individuals donating work to the nation through the Acceptance in Lieu (AIL) Scheme, administered by the Arts Council, can specify which institution will receive it. In the case of the Portrait of Oliver Porter by Sir Anthony van Dyck, it was made a condition of the offer that the painting be allocated to the Bowes Museum. The painting is a significant acquisition for the North-East and will feature in the Bowes Museum’s forthcoming major exhibition, The English Rose – Feminine Beauty from Van Dyck to Sargent, which opens in May 2016.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-12-11T16:28:42.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432917/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432917/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432917/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-11-27","Bowes Museum: Art Works","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, for what reasons the portrait of Oliver Porter by Sir Anthony van Dyck donated to the nation by the Duke of Northumberland is hung in Bowes Museum; and what discussions were held on hanging that portrait in a museum which is free to the public.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","18049"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432918","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-07","<p>The decision to withdraw the High Security Vehicle from service on 31 July 2015 was made in February 2015.</p><p>Decisions and timings on the routes to be used for the transportation of Defence Nuclear Material are part of the operational planning process. I am withholding further information as its disclosure would, or would be likely to prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p><br />","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","18046","2015-12-07T16:53:08.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432918/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432918/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432918/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-27","Radioactive Materials: Transport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answers of 21 October 2015 to Questions 12114 and 12115, on what date Defence Equipment and Support made the decision that the High Security Vehicle should be withdrawn from service on 31 July 2015.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","18060"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432919","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-02","<p>The ability of the Queen Elizabeth Class (QEC) Aircraft Carrier to support F-35B vertical landings has been incorporated into the design from the outset. The cost of preparing the flight deck was included in the revised cost of £6.2 billion announced by the previous Defence Secretary, my right hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Philip Hammond), on 6 November 2013, (Official Report, column 251-254).</p><br /><p>For information on the modifications being made to the flight deck of the QEC Aircraft Carrier, I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 12 June 2014 (Official Report, column 237W) to the right hon. Member for Moray (Angus Robertson).</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","18057","2015-12-02T16:39:41.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432919/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432919/answer","20140612_199115_Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft.docx","20140612_199115_Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft.docx","199115 - Hansard extract on Joint Strike Fighter","199115 - Hansard extract on Joint Strike Fighter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432919/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-27","HMS Queen Elizabeth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the cost will be of the safe landing modifications required to the flight deck of the aircraft carrier HMS Queen Elizabeth; and what the implications for those additional costs are for the total cost before operational use of that carrier.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","18081"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432920","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>Watchkeeper is expected to achieve full operating capability in the second quarter of 2017.</p><p>The original cost estimate for the development and delivery of Watchkeeper to full operating capability, at the time of Main Gate approval in 2005, was £847 million.</p><p>With regards to the cost of each Watchkeeper, I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 28 October 2014 to question 211342 to the hon. Member for Moray (Angus Robertson).</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","18063 ; 18064","2015-12-03T16:41:43.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432920/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432920/answer","Hansard  Extract 28 October 2014.docx","Hansard  Extract 28 October 2014.docx","Unmanned Air Vehicles","Unmanned Air Vehicles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432920/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-27","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 26 November 2015 to Question 17136, on what date Watchkeeper is expected to be at full operating capability.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","18062"
