"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432922","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-03","<p>Watchkeeper is expected to achieve full operating capability in the second quarter of 2017.</p><p>The original cost estimate for the development and delivery of Watchkeeper to full operating capability, at the time of Main Gate approval in 2005, was £847 million.</p><p>With regards to the cost of each Watchkeeper, I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 28 October 2014 to question 211342 to the hon. Member for Moray (Angus Robertson).</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","18062 ; 18063","2015-12-03T16:41:43.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432922/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432922/answer","Hansard  Extract 28 October 2014.docx","Hansard  Extract 28 October 2014.docx","Unmanned Air Vehicles","Unmanned Air Vehicles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432922/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-27","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 26 November 2015 to Question 17136, what his Department's original estimate was for the development and delivery of Watchkeeper to full operating capability.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","18064"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432923","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-02","<p>The ability of the Queen Elizabeth Class (QEC) Aircraft Carrier to support F-35B vertical landings has been incorporated into the design from the outset. The cost of preparing the flight deck was included in the revised cost of £6.2 billion announced by the previous Defence Secretary, my right hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Philip Hammond), on 6 November 2013, (Official Report, column 251-254).</p><br /><p>For information on the modifications being made to the flight deck of the QEC Aircraft Carrier, I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 12 June 2014 (Official Report, column 237W) to the right hon. Member for Moray (Angus Robertson).</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","18081","2015-12-02T16:39:42.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432923/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432923/answer","20140612_199115_Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft.docx","20140612_199115_Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft.docx","199115 - Hansard extract on Joint Strike Fighter","199115 - Hansard extract on Joint Strike Fighter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432923/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-27","HMS Queen Elizabeth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what modifications his Department is making to the flight deck of HMS Queen Elizabeth to allow the safe landing of F35 aircraft.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","18057"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432924","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-07","<p>The decision to withdraw the High Security Vehicle from service on 31 July 2015 was made in February 2015.</p><p>Decisions and timings on the routes to be used for the transportation of Defence Nuclear Material are part of the operational planning process. I am withholding further information as its disclosure would, or would be likely to prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p><br />","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","18060","2015-12-07T16:53:08.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432924/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432924/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432924/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-27","Radioactive Materials: Transport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when the decision was made by Defence Equipment and Support to transport special nuclear materials through Glasgow on 29 July 2015.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","18046"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432925","Department for Education","false","2015-12-03","<p>We will set the Department’s individual budgets as part of the internal business planning process. We will announce the future of specific programmes in due course.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2015-12-03T16:09:23.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432925/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432925/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432925/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-11-27","Carers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what funding her Department plans to allocate for specialist services for kinship carers in the period to March 2019.","false","Biography information for Alan Johnson","Kingston upon Hull West and Hessle","Alan Johnson","18033"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432926","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-12-02","<p>Chinese investment in new nuclear power stations was not a factor in our assessment of the impact of changes to government support for renewables.</p><br /> <br />","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-12-02T10:10:23.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432926/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432926/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432926/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-11-27","Renewable Energy: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how her Department took into account the planned Chinese government involvement in the construction of new nuclear energy facilities in its impact assessment on removal of market support mechanisms for wind and solar energy.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","18032"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432927","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-12-04","<p>Following consultation, state aid clearance and necessary amendments to Renewables Obligation and Feed in Tariff scheme legislation, we intend to switch from compensation to exemptions as soon as possible.</p><br /> <br />","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-12-04T12:49:20.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432927/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432927/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432927/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-11-27","Energy Intensive Industries: Trade Competitiveness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, with reference to paragraph 1.203 of the Spending Review and Autumn Statement 2015, when the energy intensive industry exemption from the cost of Renewable Obligation and Feed-in Tariff will come into effect.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","18035"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432928","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-12-02","<p>A reformed domestic supplier obligation (ECO) from April 2017 will upgrade the energy efficiency of well over 200,000 homes per year. This will help to tackle the root cause of fuel poverty and continue to deliver on our commitment to help 1 million more homes this Parliament.</p><br /><p>We are providing support for households to improve their energy efficiency through the new supplier obligation, which will run for 5 years.</p><br /><p>Our extension of the Warm Home Discount to 2020/21 at current levels of £320m pa will alsohelp households who are at most risk of fuel poverty with their energy bills.</p><p><br> <br></p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-12-02T17:03:23.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432928/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432928/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432928/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-11-27","Housing: Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, if she will take steps to develop and fund a new home energy efficiency programme.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","18034"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432929","Department of Health","false","2015-12-03","<p>This is a matter for the Lancashire Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust.</p><br /><p>We have written to Stuart Heys, Chair of the Lancashire Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust informing him of the hon. Member’s enquiry. He will reply shortly and a copy of the letter will be placed in the Library.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2015-12-03T15:00:48.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432929/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432929/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432929/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-27","Lancashire Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust: Cycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what facilities are provided by Lancashire Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust on its premises for the use of cyclists.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","18053"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432930","Department of Health","false","2015-12-03","<p>The Care Quality Commission (CQC) is the independent regulator of health and adult social acre in England. The CQC publishes the results of its new inspections regime including ratings on its website to help people choose care.</p><br /><p>The CQC website provides a search facility for the services registered with it, including care homes. It is possible to search by name of provider or post code area. The results may be viewed as a list or on an interactive map and may also be downloaded on a spreadsheet. In this way, the CQC provides flexible access to the most up to date information of the sectors it inspects.</p><br /><p>The Department expects the CQC to consider how it presents information to the public to ensure it is provided in a transparent and meaningful way and to keep its presentation of information under review.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-12-03T17:12:22.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432930/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432930/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432930/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-27","Care Homes: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 29 October 2015 to Question 12813, what assessment he has made of the accessibility, clarity and ease of comparison of the care home ratings referred to; and if he will encourage the Care Quality Commission to develop a ratings table to increase transparency of that data.","false","Biography information for Charlotte Leslie","Bristol North West","Charlotte Leslie","18036"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432931","Department of Health","false","2015-12-04","<p>Information is not held centrally on how many children in England required 24-hour care due to life-limiting or life-threatening conditions in 2014-15. The local clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) do not collect information for the North East and Sunderland.</p><br /><p>CCGs (and in the case of specialised services, NHS England), will commission a range of care to support children with life-limiting and life-threatening conditions, including paediatric care, and community-based nursing. A child with a life-limiting condition may be eligible for a package of continuing care, where their needs are such that they require clinical care in addition to that routinely commissioned. This might include one-to-one support. NHS England also allocates an annual grant of £11 million to children’s hospices to support their provision of palliative and respite care.</p><br /><p>Children and young people with complex needs may also be eligible for local authority-commissioned social care to support living, short-breaks, and special educational support, where they have a special educational need.</p><br /> <br /> <br />","Battersea","Jane Ellison","18086","2015-12-04T14:43:45.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432931/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432931/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432931/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-27","Health Services: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many children in (a) England, (b) the North East and (c) Sunderland required 24-hour care due to life-limiting or life-threatening conditions in 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","18044"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432932","Department of Health","false","2015-12-04","<p>Information is not held centrally on how many children in England required 24-hour care due to life-limiting or life-threatening conditions in 2014-15. The local clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) do not collect information for the North East and Sunderland.</p><br /><p>CCGs (and in the case of specialised services, NHS England), will commission a range of care to support children with life-limiting and life-threatening conditions, including paediatric care, and community-based nursing. A child with a life-limiting condition may be eligible for a package of continuing care, where their needs are such that they require clinical care in addition to that routinely commissioned. This might include one-to-one support. NHS England also allocates an annual grant of £11 million to children’s hospices to support their provision of palliative and respite care.</p><br /><p>Children and young people with complex needs may also be eligible for local authority-commissioned social care to support living, short-breaks, and special educational support, where they have a special educational need.</p><br /> <br /> <br />","Battersea","Jane Ellison","18044","2015-12-04T14:43:46.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432932/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432932/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432932/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-27","Health Services: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what support is offered to families with children suffering from life-limiting or life-threatening conditions in England.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","18086"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432933","Department of Health","false","2015-12-02","<br /><p>The Department of Health’s Visitor and Migrant National Health Service Cost Recovery Programme aims to ensure that the National Health Service receives a fair contribution for the cost of healthcare it provides to non-United Kingdom residents and improve the amount of costs recovered from them or their home countries, to ensure the NHS is sustainable.</p><br /><p>Since the launch of its implementation plan in July 2014 the Cost Recovery Programme has achieved much progress including:</p><br /><p>- The launch of the European Health Insurance Card (EHIC) reporting incentive scheme in October 2014 to improve the reporting of EHIC details of visitors and students from the European Economic Area (EEA) who access NHS care, for which the UK is entitled to reimbursement.</p><br /><p>- Updated Charging Regulations from April 2015, reducing the number of exemption from charge categories for non-residents and realigning the Regulations to the principle that the NHS is a residency-based healthcare system.</p><br /><p>- Requiring chargeable patients from outside the EEA to be charged at 150% of national tariff, in tandem with the launch of a risk sharing arrangement with commissioners, thereby encouraging providers to both identify and recover costs from these patients to access the extra funding available.</p><br /><p>- The introduction of the health surcharge in April 2015 which now means nearly all individuals who require a visa to remain in the UK for more than six month’s pay an annual surcharge as a contribution towards their healthcare costs.</p><br /><p>Furthermore, those with outstanding debts to the NHS of £1,000 or more and who are subject to immigration control can, since 2011, have applications for new visas or extensions of stay refused because of that debt, to encourage them to pay it.</p><br />","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-12-02T17:13:42.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432933/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432933/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432933/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-27","Health Services: Foreign Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department has taken to reclaim the costs to the NHS of treatment of people from other countries who use NHS services while visiting the UK.","false","Biography information for Anne Marie Morris","Newton Abbot","Anne Marie Morris","18090"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432934","Home Office","false","2015-12-02","<p>The Home Office does not hold the information asked for.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-12-02T14:38:38.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432934/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432934/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432934/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-11-27","Police: Abu Dhabi","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, on what dates officers of the Metropolitan Police Service trained officers of the Security Support Department of the Abu Dhabi Police; how many such officers were trained; what the content of that training was; and whether that training included training on human rights issues.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","18047"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432935","Department for International Development","false","2015-12-03","<p>DFID provides no bilateral aid to Brazil. As such, DFID does not provide any support to protect the Amazon rainforest from deforestation. DFID does provide support to stop deforestation in other developing countries, such as Indonesia, Liberia, and the Central Africa region, and this is a key priority for UK climate finance.</p><br /><p>DFID’s relationship with Brazil focuses on working together in partnership to reduce poverty and achieve sustainable development in other developing countries.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2015-12-03T16:39:21.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432935/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432935/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432935/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-11-27","Amazonia: Rain Forests","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what funding her Department provides to support efforts to protect the Amazon rainforest from deforestation; and what recent assessment she has made of the effectiveness of that funding.","false","Biography information for Ben Howlett","Bath","Ben Howlett","18087"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432936","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-12-02","<p>Details of all Ministerial meetings are included in transparency returns which are published quarterly on <a href="http://gov.uk" target="_blank">gov.uk</a>.</p><br /><p>As part of policy making, the Ministry of Justice engages with a wide range of stakeholders.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2015-12-02T16:24:02.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432936/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432936/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432936/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-11-27","Ministry of Justice: Meetings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what meetings (a) Ministers and (b) officials in his Department have had with (i) insurance companies, (ii) claimant personal injury solicitors and (iii) defendant personal injury solicitors since the 2015 General Election; and who attended any such meeting.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","18082"
