"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432941","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-12-02","<p>We have received no such formal representation. Ministry of Justice Ministers have met the Secretary General of the Council of Europe Jagland, the UN High Commissioner for Human Rights Zeid, and the UN Special Rapporteur on the promotion of truth, justice, reparation and guarantees of non-recurrence de Greiff.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2015-12-02T17:58:12.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432941/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432941/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432941/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-11-27","European Convention on Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what recent representations he has received from (a) the Council of Europe, (b) the UN and (c) other international bodies on the UK's membership of the European Convention on Human Rights.","false","Biography information for Nick Thomas-Symonds","Torfaen","Nick Thomas-Symonds","18042"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432942","Prime Minister","false","2015-12-02","<p>We have regular discussions with fellow members of the International Syria Support Group (ISSG), which includes the US, France and regional partners, about our strategy for tackling Daesh. The most recent ministerial meeting of the ISSG took place in Vienna on 14 November. We expect that a further meeting will take place in December. Such fora are an important means making steps towards the common goal of achieving a political solution to the Syria crisis and the defeat of ISIL. We will continue to play a leading, active role as a member of the ISSG.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-12-02T16:38:58.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432942/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432942/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432942/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-11-27","Syria: Islamic State","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, pursuant to his Oral Statement of 26 November 2015, Official Report, columns 1489-94, what representations he has received from members of the International Syria Support Group on his proposed strategy for tackling ISIL.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","18058"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432943","Prime Minister","false","2015-12-02","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave to the hon. Member for Brighton, Pavilion (Ms Lucas) on 1 December 2015, UIN 17826 and 17854, and to the answer I gave to my right hon. Friend the Member for New Forest East (Dr Lewis) of the same date, UIN 18014.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-12-02T16:33:50.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432943/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432943/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432943/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-11-27","Syria: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, pursuant to his Oral Statement of 26 November 2015, Official Report, columns 1489-94, what assessment he has made of the reliability of the 70,000 ground forces referred to as international partners in the fight against Daesh.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","18084"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432944","Prime Minister","false","2015-12-02","<p>Coalition airstrikes have been on-going since September 2014. Airstrikes may cause some local level internal displacement and disruption; but it is the conflict that is the main cause of suffering and displacement of civilians in Syria.</p><br /><p>The UK has been at the forefront of the response to the crisis in Syria and the region. We have pledged over £1.1 billion, our largest ever response to a single humanitarian crisis. We are the second largest bilateral donor after the US. UK support has reached hundreds of thousands of people in Syria, Jordan, Lebanon, Turkey, Iraq and Egypt. By the end of June 2015, UK support inside Syria and in the surrounding region had, for example, delivered almost 20 million food rations that feed one person for a month; over 2.5 million medical consultations; and relief items for 4.6 million people.</p><br /><p>The UK is supporting refugees to remain in host countries in the region, and supporting host countries to accommodate them As part of this, we are working in partnership with host countries to help them to expand job and education opportunities for refugees in a way that will enable them to better support themselves and give them skills for the future, and we are helping host countries to cope with the impact of refugees on local services.</p><br /><p>We will continue the work parallel with proposals to expand military operations in the country.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-12-02T16:35:40.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432944/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432944/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432944/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-11-27","Syria: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, pursuant to his Oral Statement of 26 November 2015, Official Report, columns 1489-94, what assessment the Government has made of the potential increased displacement of people in Syria of his proposal to extend military operations to that country; and what the implications of that assessment are for the Government's policy on the number of Syrian refugees.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","18083"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432945","Prime Minister","false","2015-12-02","<p>Coalition airstrikes have been on-going since September 2014. Airstrikes may cause some local level internal displacement and disruption; but it is the conflict that is the main cause of suffering of civilians in Syria. In Syria, the UN carries out regular humanitarian contingency planning exercises including preparing for the impact of military operations.</p><br /><p>To date, the UK has allocated £559 million to support refugees in the region and vulnerable host communities, including £304 million in Lebanon, £193 million in Jordan and the remainder across the region.</p><br /><p>The UK is very concerned about the plight of the Syrian people. This is why the Prime Minister announced on 16 November that the UK, Kuwait, Norway, Germany and the UN will co-host an international conference on the Syria crisis in London on 4 February 2016. The Conference aims to raise significant new funding to meet the needs of all those affected by crisis within Syria and to support neighbouring countries, who have shown enormous generosity in hosting refugees, to cope with the impact of the crisis. The Conference will aim to raise both emergency and long-term funding for 2016 and subsequent years.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-12-02T16:37:05.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432945/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432945/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432945/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-11-27","Syria: Humanitarian Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, pursuant to his Oral Statement of 26 November 2015, Official Report, columns 1489-94, what additional humanitarian support the Government plans to provide to countries that border Syria to assist with the likely increased displacement of people as a result of the coordinated international response to Daesh in Syria.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","18085"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432946","Department for Transport","false","2015-12-04","<p>The Government is currently considering the large amount of very detailed analysis contained in the Airports Commission’s final report before taking any decisions on next steps.</p><br /><p>The Government will carefully consider all the evidence set out, including that on costs, when making a decision on additional runway capacity.</p><br />","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","18065 ; 18066 ; 18067 ; 18068 ; 18069 ; 18071 ; 18072 ; 18073 ; 18074 ; 18075 ; 18076 ; 18077 ; 18078","2015-12-04T14:25:08.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432946/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432946/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432946/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-27","London Airports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the Airports Commission estimate of net present value of the three shortlisted schemes took account of the (a) extent to which the cost of each such scheme would be passed to passengers in higher fares and (b) effect of such higher fares on passenger demand.","false","Biography information for Lord Tyrie","Chichester","Mr Andrew Tyrie","18070"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432947","Department for Transport","false","2015-12-04","<p>The Government is currently considering the large amount of very detailed analysis contained in the Airports Commission’s final report before taking any decisions on next steps.</p><br /><p>The Government will carefully consider all the evidence set out, including that on costs, when making a decision on additional runway capacity.</p><br />","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","18065 ; 18066 ; 18067 ; 18068 ; 18070 ; 18071 ; 18072 ; 18073 ; 18074 ; 18075 ; 18076 ; 18077 ; 18078","2015-12-04T14:25:08.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432947/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432947/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432947/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-27","London Airports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the Airports Commission estimated the probability that the net present value of the three shortlisted schemes would be zero or negative; and what that probability was for each shortlisted scheme under the carbon capped and carbon traded policy frameworks.","false","Biography information for Lord Tyrie","Chichester","Mr Andrew Tyrie","18069"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432948","Department for Transport","false","2015-12-04","<p>The Government is currently considering the large amount of very detailed analysis contained in the Airports Commission’s final report before taking any decisions on next steps.</p><br /><p>The Government will carefully consider all the evidence set out, including that on costs, when making a decision on additional runway capacity.</p><br />","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","18065 ; 18066 ; 18067 ; 18068 ; 18069 ; 18070 ; 18072 ; 18073 ; 18074 ; 18075 ; 18076 ; 18077 ; 18078","2015-12-04T14:25:08.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432948/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432948/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432948/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-27","London Airports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, for what reasons the Airports Commission used his Department's National Air Passenger Demand Model and National Air Passenger Allocation model in its work; whether the assumption of homogenous capacity in those models affected the net present value figures in Table 7.1 of the Commission's Final Report, published in July 2015, compared with a model that distinguished between long and short-haul, business and leisure, and domestic and international capacity; and what assessment he has made of whether the use of a model that distinguishes between such different types of capacity would increase or decrease the net present value of each of those shortlisted schemes.","false","Biography information for Lord Tyrie","Chichester","Mr Andrew Tyrie","18071"
